STEP 1: Install Requirements
command to be used
    pip install flask flask-socketio pyngrok
STEP 2: Create Python File
Open Notepad
give the code 
Save as
  honeypot.py
make sure the file in 
  C:\Users\YourName\
STEP 3: Clean Old Database
Delete old DB to avoid empty charts
command to be used 
    del honeypot.db
STEP 4: Setup Ngrok
1. Create account
   Go to: https://dashboard.ngrok.com/signup
2. Copy your auth token
3. Add token in Command prompt
         ngrok config add-authtoken YOUR_TOKEN
STEP 5: Run the Project
     python honeypot.py
You should see
Listening on 2222
Listening on 8080
[SIM] Running...
Public Dashboard: https://xxxxx.ngrok-free.dev
STEP 6: Open Dashboard
Open browser and visit
      https://xxxxx.ngrok-free.dev
STEP 7: Verify It’s Working
Within 2–5 seconds, you should see
Charts moving
Logs updating
Numbers increasing

